Sonar is complaining because `dummyEndpoint(...)` has an empty body.

Since this method exists only to create a `MethodParameter` for the test, just add an explanatory comment inside it:

```java
@SuppressWarnings("unused")
private void dummyEndpoint(
        @RequestHeader("APP_ID") String appId
) {
    // Test fixture method used only to create a MethodParameter instance.
}
```

That should satisfy the rule.

You do not need to throw `UnsupportedOperationException`, because the method is never supposed to execute. Adding the comment is the cleanest option for a test helper.
